{"id":2166,"date":"2022-06-06T16:10:25","date_gmt":"2022-06-06T16:10:25","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/robotics.gabysoft.com\/?page_id=2166"},"modified":"2022-06-06T16:15:13","modified_gmt":"2022-06-06T16:15:13","slug":"configuring-putty","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/configuring-putty\/","title":{"rendered":"Configuring PuTTY"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>To configure the&nbsp;<strong>PuTTY<\/strong>&nbsp;program, double click on the&nbsp;<strong>putty.exe<\/strong>&nbsp;program that is in the&nbsp;<strong>PiUtils<\/strong>&nbsp;folder. The&nbsp;<strong>PuTTY<\/strong>&nbsp;configuration window should look like:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"602\" height=\"537\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-83\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty1.jpg 602w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty1-300x268.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 602px) 100vw, 602px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Let\u2019s test to see if we can connect to the robot. Enter the IP address&nbsp;<strong>172.24.1.1<\/strong>&nbsp;into the&nbsp;<strong>Host Name (or IP address)<\/strong>&nbsp;field and enter the name&nbsp;<strong>Robot<\/strong>&nbsp;in the&nbsp;<strong>Saved Sessions<\/strong>&nbsp;field and click&nbsp;<strong>Save<\/strong>. Then click&nbsp;<strong>Open<\/strong>&nbsp;and the following window should appear:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/johngaby-001-site7.gtempurl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LogIn.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/johngaby-001-site7.gtempurl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LogIn.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2110\" width=\"617\" height=\"390\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LogIn.jpg 825w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LogIn-300x189.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LogIn-150x95.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/LogIn-768x485.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 617px) 100vw, 617px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Log in using the user name&nbsp;<strong>pi<\/strong>&nbsp;and password&nbsp;<strong>raspberry<\/strong>. Note that when you type in the password, the keys you type will&nbsp;<strong>not<\/strong>&nbsp;be echoed so you have to type in the password blind.&nbsp; Once you get this working, close the&nbsp;<strong>PuTTY<\/strong>&nbsp;window.&nbsp; If this window does not appear, check to make sure that your WiFi is connected to your robot.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We now want to configure the session so that it automatically logs in and starts the remote launcher program on the <strong>pi<\/strong>. Once again, double click on the&nbsp;<strong>putty.exe<\/strong>&nbsp;program. Then click on the&nbsp;<strong>Robot<\/strong>&nbsp;session and click&nbsp;<strong>Load<\/strong>. &nbsp;Now click on the&nbsp;<strong>Connection\/Data<\/strong>&nbsp;option on the left and enter&nbsp;<strong>pi<\/strong>&nbsp;in the&nbsp;<strong>Auto-login username<\/strong>&nbsp;field like this:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"602\" height=\"537\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-89\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty3.jpg 602w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty3-300x268.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 602px) 100vw, 602px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now click on the&nbsp;<strong>Connection\/SSH<\/strong>&nbsp;option on the left and enter&nbsp;<strong>.\/run<\/strong>&nbsp;in the&nbsp;<strong>Remote command<\/strong>&nbsp;field, as follows:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"602\" height=\"537\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-91\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty4.jpg 602w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty4-300x268.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 602px) 100vw, 602px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, click on the&nbsp;<strong>Session<\/strong>&nbsp;option on the left and change the&nbsp;<strong>Saved Sessions<\/strong>&nbsp;name to&nbsp;<strong>Robot.Run<\/strong>, then click&nbsp;<strong>Save<\/strong>&nbsp;to save this session.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"602\" height=\"537\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty5.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-92\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty5.jpg 602w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty5-300x268.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 602px) 100vw, 602px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now test this out by clicking the&nbsp;<strong>Open<\/strong>&nbsp;button. &nbsp;If everything is set up correctly, the terminal window should open and ask for your password. Enter&nbsp;<strong>raspberry<\/strong>&nbsp;as the password, and you should then see the following:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><a href=\"http:\/\/johngaby-001-site7.gtempurl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Login2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/johngaby-001-site7.gtempurl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Login2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2112\" width=\"610\" height=\"384\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Login2.jpg 825w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Login2-300x189.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Login2-150x95.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Login2-768x485.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 610px) 100vw, 610px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>When you have this working, close the&nbsp;<strong>PuTTY<\/strong>&nbsp;window.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now we want to create a second&nbsp;<strong>PuTTY<\/strong>&nbsp;session which we can use to shutdown the&nbsp;<strong>Pi<\/strong>&nbsp;gracefully. Launch&nbsp;<strong>PuTTY<\/strong>&nbsp;again, click on the&nbsp;<strong>Robot.Run<\/strong>&nbsp;entry and click&nbsp;<strong>Load<\/strong>. Then change the&nbsp;<strong>Saved Sessions<\/strong>&nbsp;name to&nbsp;<strong>Robot.Shutdown<\/strong>&nbsp;as shown and click&nbsp;<strong>Save<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"602\" height=\"537\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty6.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-96\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty6.jpg 602w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty6-300x268.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 602px) 100vw, 602px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then click on the&nbsp;<strong>SSH<\/strong>&nbsp;Category on the left and change the&nbsp;<strong>Remote command<\/strong>&nbsp;field as follows:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"602\" height=\"537\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty7.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-97\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty7.jpg 602w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/Putty7-300x268.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 602px) 100vw, 602px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, click back on the&nbsp;<strong>Session<\/strong>&nbsp;Category and click the&nbsp;<strong>Save<\/strong>&nbsp;button and close the&nbsp;<strong>PuTTY<\/strong>&nbsp;window.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>To configure the&nbsp;PuTTY&nbsp;program, double click on the&nbsp;putty.exe&nbsp;program that is in the&nbsp;PiUtils&nbsp;fold